#stance=stance2
#originalStanceText=At Conception
#originalTopic=when-does-life-begin
People always forget about Doe v. Bolton, which was decided on the same day as Roe.  Doe allows   abortion   after viability in order to protect the health of the mother, with health being defined in a very broad fashion.Consequently, atrocities like late-term abortions and partial-birth abortions are permitted, despite the viability standard established in Roe.